The paper deals with the analysis of algorithms and data structures on hypergraphs, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of k-core is a fundamental concept in graph theory and is closely related to data structures and algorithms, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.DS (data structures) or cs.GR (graph theory). The paper also discusses the edge density threshold, which is a probabilistic concept and could be related to cs.PF (probability). Finally, the paper discusses parallel implementation using GPUs, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (computational complexity).
